    "id": "aws-28",
    "category": "AWS",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "Write a CloudWatch Logs Insights query to find the top 10 IP addresses requesting a specific URI that returned HTTP 500 errors in your Application Load Balancer access logs.",
    "answer": "CloudWatch Logs Insights queries parse and filter logs using custom query syntax.\n\n```logquery\nfields @timestamp, client_ip, request_url, status\n| filter status = 500\n| filter request_url like \"/api/checkout\"\n| stats count(*) as errorCount by client_ip\n| sort errorCount desc\n| limit 10\n```\n\n**Explanation**:\n- `fields`: Identifies the attributes extracted from the log pattern.\n- `filter status = 500`: Targets the specific HTTP response code.\n- `filter request_url like ...`: Targets requests matching the checkout API path.\n- `stats count(*) ... by client_ip`: Aggregates the counts of occurrences per IP address.\n- `sort ... desc`: Sorts the output to place the heaviest consumers (or potential attackers) at the top.",
    "tags": [
      "CloudWatch",
      "Logs Insights",
      "Troubleshooting",
      "Monitoring",
      "ALB"
    ]
