    "id": "aws-35",
    "category": "AWS",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "How do you set up Amazon S3 Cross-Region Replication (CRR) for an encrypted bucket? What IAM permissions are required for the replication role?",
    "answer": "S3 CRR requires S3 versioning enabled on both source and destination buckets.\n\n**Setup Steps**:\n1. Enable versioning on both buckets.\n2. **Create IAM Replication Role**: The role allows S3 to read from the source bucket and write to the destination bucket, and decrypt/encrypt using KMS keys:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\n     \"Statement\": [\n       { \"Effect\": \"Allow\", \"Action\": [\"s3:GetObjectVersionForReplication\", \"s3:GetObjectVersionAcl\"], \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::source-bucket/*\" },\n       { \"Effect\": \"Allow\", \"Action\": [\"s3:ReplicateObject\", \"s3:ReplicateDelete\"], \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::dest-bucket/*\" },\n       { \"Effect\": \"Allow\", \"Action\": [\"kms:Decrypt\"], \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:kms:us-east-1:account:key/source-key-id\" },\n       { \"Effect\": \"Allow\", \"Action\": [\"kms:Encrypt\"], \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:us-west-2:account:key/dest-key-id\" }\n     ]\n   }\n   ```\n3. **Apply Replication Configuration**: Define a replication rule on the source bucket, specifying the destination bucket, the replication IAM role, and enable KMS decryption support.",
