    "id": "docker-4",
    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "How do you enable BuildKit in Docker, and what are its primary advantages over the legacy builder?",
    "answer": "BuildKit can be enabled by setting the environment variable DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1 before running docker build, or by configuring it as default in /etc/docker/daemon.json:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \"features\": {\\n    \"buildkit\": true\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nKey advantages of BuildKit include:\\n1. Parallel execution of independent build stages.\\n2. Incremental build caching and remote cache exportation.\\n3. Advanced mount features like bind, cache (--mount=type=cache), and secret mounting (--mount=type=secret).\\n4. SSH forwarding support.",
