    "id": "docker-7",
    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "How can you run a Docker container with drops/additions of Linux capabilities to enforce the principle of least privilege?",
    "answer": "By default, Docker containers run with a restricted set of Linux capabilities. However, SREs can further restrict capabilities using the --cap-drop and --cap-add flags during container execution.\\n\\nTo drop all default capabilities and add back only the ability to bind to privileged ports below 1024, execute:\\n```bash\\ndocker run --cap-drop=ALL --cap-add=NET_BIND_SERVICE -d nginx\\n```\\nThis drastically reduces the attack surface if the application inside the container is compromised, as it cannot perform arbitrary root operations (like loading kernel modules or modifying network routing).",
    "tags": [
      "Security",
      "Capabilities",
      "Hardening"
    ]
