    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "How do Docker Compose profiles work, and how do you launch services dynamically based on profiles?",
    "answer": "Profiles in Docker Compose allow you to define services that are only started under specific conditions or workflows (e.g., local development, running tests, or debugging tools), keeping the compose file unified.\\n\\nExample service configuration in docker-compose.yml:\\n```yaml\\nservices:\\n  debug-console:\\n    image: debug-tool\\n    profiles: [\"debug\"]\\n```\\nBy default, running `docker compose up` will skip the `debug-console` service. To launch it along with default services, execute:\\n```bash\\ndocker compose --profile debug up\\n```",
