    "id": "docker-10",
    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "Write a docker inspect command to extract the IP address of a running container.",
    "answer": "The `docker inspect` command returns detailed JSON metadata for a container. You can use Go templates via the `--format` or `-f` flag to extract nested values directly without external parsing tools (like jq).\\n\\nTo extract the IP address of a container named `web-app` for its default bridge network, run:\\n```bash\\ndocker inspect -f '{{range .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{.IPAddress}}{{end}}' web-app\\n```\\nTo get it from a specific network named `my-net`:\\n```bash\\ndocker inspect -f '{{.NetworkSettings.Networks.my_net.IPAddress}}' web-app\\n```",
