    "question": "In Docker Compose V2, how do you verify that a database container is fully healthy before starting dependent services?",
    "answer": "Docker Compose V2 allows you to leverage healthchecks in combination with the `depends_on` instruction to control startup order based on service health rather than just process execution.\\n\\nExample Configuration:\\n```yaml\\nservices:\\n  db:\\n    image: postgres:15-alpine\\n    healthcheck:\\n      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U postgres\"]\\n      interval: 5s\\n      timeout: 5s\\n      retries: 5\\n  web:\\n    image: node-app\\n    depends_on:\\n      db:\\n        condition: service_healthy\\n```\\nThis forces the web application container to delay startup until Postgres passes its pg_isready check.",
