    "question": "How can you share a network namespace between two containers, and when is this pattern useful?",
    "answer": "You can launch a container and instruct it to join the network namespace of an existing container using the `--net=container:<container_name_or_id>` flag.\\n\\nExample:\\n```bash\\n# Run database\\ndocker run -d --name db redis\\n# Run debug utility sharing the db network namespace\\ndocker run -it --net=container:db nicolaka/netshoot tcpdump -i any\\n```\\n**Usefulness**: This is identical to the Kubernetes Pod model (where multiple containers share a single infra Pause container network). It is highly useful for local debugging (capturing traffic, monitoring ports via localhost), sidecar patterns, or executing diagnostics without installing tools in the main application image.",
