    "question": "How does Docker Buildx/BuildKit compile multi-platform images, and what roles do QEMU and binfmt_misc play?",
    "answer": "Docker Buildx leverages BuildKit and QEMU to cross-compile images for alternate architectures (e.g., building arm64 on an amd64 host).\\n\\n**How it works**:\\n1. The host kernel's `binfmt_misc` module is configured to recognize non-native binary formats.\\n2. When BuildKit encounters a non-native command in a stage (e.g., executing arm64 code), the kernel delegates execution to the registered QEMU emulator binary (like `/usr/bin/qemu-aarch64-static`) running inside the build environment.\\n\\nExample command:\\n```bash\\ndocker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 -t my-registry/app:latest --push .\\n```",
