    "question": "Explain the environment variable precedence rules in Docker Compose V2.",
    "answer": "When variables are defined in multiple places, Docker Compose V2 resolves them in the following order of precedence (highest to lowest):\\n1. **Compose file**: Explicitly defined in the `environment` block within the service configuration.\\n2. **Shell environment**: Variables set in the host terminal running the docker compose command.\\n3. **Environment file**: Variables defined in the `--env-file` CLI flag.\\n4. **Default env file**: Variables defined in the `.env` file located in the project root directory.\\n5. **Image configuration**: Variables defined using `ENV` instructions in the Dockerfile.",
