    "question": "How do you debug container DNS resolution issues from the host when the container lacks diagnostics tools?",
    "answer": "Production containers (like distroless or minimal images) often lack `ping`, `nslookup`, or `curl`. You can debug their network namespace directly from the host using network troubleshooting containers (like `nicolaka/netshoot`) or Linux namespace tools.\\n\\nMethod 1: Join the container's network namespace using a sidecar container:\\n```bash\\ndocker run --rm -it --net=container:<target-container-id> nicolaka/netshoot nslookup kubernetes.default\\n```\\nMethod 2: Inspect `/etc/resolv.conf` within the container namespace:\\n```bash\\ndocker exec <target-container-id> cat /etc/resolv.conf\\n```",
