    "id": "docker-37",
    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "Explain how to configure remote cache exports (e.g. registry-based cache-to/cache-from) using BuildKit in multi-tenant CI/CD pipelines.",
    "answer": "BuildKit allows exporting build caches to remote locations (like registry, GHA, or S3) so that developers and CI runners can reuse cache layers generated in separate pipelines.\\n\\nTo build and export cache to a registry, use the `max` mode (which exports intermediate and final layer caches) and import it in subsequent jobs:\\n```bash\\ndocker buildx build \\\\n  --platform linux/amd64 \\\\n  --cache-to=type=registry,ref=my-registry.local/cache/app:latest,mode=max \\\\n  --cache-from=type=registry,ref=my-registry.local/cache/app:latest \\\\n  -t my-registry.local/prod/app:1.0 --push .\\n```\\nThis prevents rebuilding unchanged base dependencies in multi-tenant runners by sharing a single registry-backed cache repository.",
