    "id": "docker-42",
    "category": "Docker",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "Explain how Docker integrates with third-party storage arrays using Docker Volume Plugins, and write a run command using an external volume driver.",
    "answer": "Docker Volume Plugins allow Docker to bypass local storage and mount remote block or file storage (like AWS EBS, NFS, or Ceph) directly to containers. The plugin intercepts volume API calls (create, mount, unmount) and translates them into storage-array-specific API calls.\\n\\nExample command using the `rexray/ebs` driver to provision and attach an AWS EBS volume dynamically:\\n```bash\\ndocker run -d \\\\n  --volume-driver=rexray/ebs \\\\n  --name database \\\\n  -v prod-db-vol:/var/lib/mysql \\\\n  mysql:8.0\\n```\\nHere, the volume plugin handles attaching the EBS volume to the AWS EC2 host and formatting it before mapping it into the container namespace.",
