    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "How do you check the logs of a container that recently crashed and is in a CrashLoopBackOff state?",
    "answer": "When a container crashes, checking `kubectl logs <pod-name>` only shows the logs of the *current* running instance, which may be empty or contain only startup logs. To view logs from the failed container instance before it restarted, use the `--previous` or `-p` flag:\\n```bash\\nkubectl logs my-pod-name -c container-name --previous\\n```\\nThis reads logs from the runtime's local log cache of the terminated container.",
