    "id": "k8s-12",
    "category": "Kubernetes",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "What is the role of CoreDNS in a Kubernetes cluster, and how do Pods know where to send DNS requests?",
    "answer": "CoreDNS is the default cluster DNS server in Kubernetes. It registers IP addresses of Services and resolves domain names internally (e.g., `my-service.my-namespace.svc.cluster.local`).\\n\\nPods know where to send DNS queries because the Kubelet injects a DNS configuration into `/etc/resolv.conf` of every container during creation. This file points to the CoreDNS Service IP address (typically the 10th IP in the Service CIDR block, e.g., 10.96.0.10) and configures search domains.",
