    "id": "k8s-36",
    "category": "Kubernetes",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "How does the Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) compute replica targets, and how does the stabilization window prevent flapping?",
    "answer": "The HPA controller queries metrics endpoints and computes the target replica count using this formula:\\n`TargetNumReplicas = ceil( CurrentNumReplicas * ( CurrentMetricValue / TargetMetricValue ) )`\\n\\n**Flapping Prevention (Stabilization Window)**: To prevent frequent scaling up and down during minor load fluctuations, the HPA controller keeps a record of all scale decisions over a historical window (default 5 minutes for scale down). It evaluates all computed target values over that time period and selects the highest replica count calculated, smoothing out scale down actions.",
    "tags": [
      "HPA",
      "Scaling",
      "Metrics"
    ]
