    "question": "How do you configure CoreDNS to forward queries for a specific external domain to an internal DNS server?",
    "answer": "You customize CoreDNS behaviour by editing the `coredns` ConfigMap in the `kube-system` namespace. You can declare specific server blocks targeting custom zones.\\n\\nExample Corefile configuration block:\\n```txt\\ncoredns.local:53 {\\n    errors\\n    cache 30\\n    forward . 192.168.10.150\\n}\\n```\\nAdding this block inside the Corefile directs CoreDNS to forward all queries matching `*.coredns.local` to the upstream DNS server at `192.168.10.150` instead of parsing them locally or sending them to the default public resolv.conf forwarders.",
