    "id": "k8s-39",
    "category": "Kubernetes",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "Design an advanced scheduling strategy combining Pod Topology Spread Constraints and Pod Anti-Affinity to run a multi-tenant HA deployment.",
    "answer": "To run a highly available application across racks and availability zones while preventing two replicas from running on the same node, combine constraints in the Deployment spec:\\n\\n```yaml\\nspec:\\n  affinity:\\n    podAntiAffinity:\\n      requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:\\n      - labelSelector:\\n          matchExpressions:\\n          - key: app\\n            operator: In\\n            values: [\"payment-api\"]\\n        topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname\\n  topologySpreadConstraints:\\n  - maxSkew: 1\\n    topologyKey: topology.kubernetes.io/zone\\n    whenUnsatisfiable: DoNotSchedule\\n    labelSelector:\\n      matchLabels:\\n        app: payment-api\\n  - maxSkew: 1\\n    topologyKey: kubernetes.io/rack\\n    whenUnsatisfiable: ScheduleAnyway\\n    labelSelector:\\n      matchLabels:\\n        app: payment-api\\n```\\nThis configuration guarantees that no node runs more than one payment-api Pod, guarantees zones are balanced strictly (DoNotSchedule), and attempts to balance pods across hardware racks on a best-effort basis (ScheduleAnyway).",
