    "id": "k8s-46",
    "category": "Kubernetes",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "How do you optimize CoreDNS for extreme scale (high-throughput service discovery) in production Kubernetes clusters?",
    "answer": "To scale CoreDNS to handle millions of queries, apply these performance enhancements:\\n1. **Enable Autoscale**: Deploy the `coredns-autoscaler` (horizontal-pod-autoscaler or proportional autoscaler) to dynamically scale replicas based on node counts or CPU metrics.\\n2. **Optimize Cache**: Increase cache capacity and TTL settings in the Corefile configuration:\\n   `cache 30 { success 10000 denial 1000 }`\\n3. **Use NodeLocal DNSCache**: Deploy NodeLocal DNSCache as a DaemonSet. It runs a lightweight DNS caching agent on every node. Pods resolve queries via localhost (`169.254.20.10`), bypassing the conntrack tables and reducing network latency to CoreDNS.",
