    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "Write a basic `.gitlab-ci.yml` pipeline configuration with two stages (build and test). Define a job in each stage.",
    "answer": "This basic configuration defines stages and maps jobs to those stages:\n\n```yaml\nstages:\n  - build\n  - test\n\nbuild-job:\n  stage: build\n  image: node:18-alpine\n  script:\n    - npm install\n    - npm run build\n\ntest-job:\n  stage: test\n  image: node:18-alpine\n  script:\n    - npm test\n```\n\nKey details:\n- `stages` defines the execution order. All jobs in `build` run in parallel. Jobs in `test` only start if all build jobs exit successfully.\n- `script` contains the actual shell commands executed on the runner host.",
