    "question": "How do you integrate JUnit test reports and container security scans so they show up directly in GitLab Merge Request widgets? Show the YAML configurations.",
    "answer": "GitLab parses structured XML and JSON artifacts to render inline reports in Merge Requests.\n\n**JUnit test report integration**:\n```yaml\ntest-job:\n  stage: test\n  script:\n    - pytest --junitxml=report.xml\n  artifacts:\n    reports:\n      junit: report.xml\n```\n\n**Container Scanning integration**:\n```yaml\nscan-image:\n  stage: test\n  script:\n    - trivy image --format json --output gl-container-scanning-report.json $IMAGE\n  artifacts:\n    reports:\n      container_scanning: gl-container-scanning-report.json\n```\nGitLab UI parses these reports and displays test failures or vulnerability lists directly in the Merge Request widget, allowing review before merging.",
