    "id": "gitlab-27",
    "category": "GitLab",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "How do you set up environment-specific deployments with manual approval gates? Write a YAML example for deploying to `production` only after manual confirmation.",
    "answer": "Manual gates are configured by combining `when: manual` inside a rules block with environment configurations.\n\n**Configuration**:\n```yaml\ndeploy-to-prod:\n  stage: deploy\n  environment:\n    name: production\n    url: https://my-app.com\n  script:\n    - ./deploy_code.sh\n  rules:\n    - if: '$CI_COMMIT_BRANCH == \"main\"'\n      when: manual # Requires manual click in the GitLab UI to execute\n      allow_failure: false # Ensures pipeline doesn't show green unless manual step is executed/skipped\n    - when: never\n```\nWhen the pipeline reaches the deploy stage, it pauses on `deploy-to-prod`. Only users with Deployment permissions to the production environment can click the play button to trigger the deploy script.",
