    "id": "gitlab-31",
    "category": "GitLab",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "How do you use the `parallel` keyword to distribute tests across multiple concurrent jobs? Show a matrix configuration mapping Python versions.",
    "answer": "The `parallel: matrix` keyword spawns multiple jobs in the same stage, running them concurrently with different variable combinations.\n\n**Python Test Matrix Example**:\n```yaml\ntest-matrix:\n  stage: test\n  image: python:${PYTHON_VERSION}\n  parallel:\n    matrix:\n      - PYTHON_VERSION: [\"3.8\", \"3.9\", \"3.10\"]\n        DB_PROVIDER: [\"sqlite\", \"postgres\"]\n  script:\n    - python --version\n    - pytest --db $DB_PROVIDER\n```\nThis configuration generates **six parallel jobs** concurrently (e.g. `test-matrix: [3.8, sqlite]`, `test-matrix: [3.8, postgres]`, etc.). This is a clean way to validate cross-platform compliance without duplicating HCL/YAML configurations.",
