    "id": "gitlab-32",
    "category": "GitLab",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "How do you configure GitLab CI/CD to authenticate to cloud providers (AWS, GCP) without using long-lived credentials? Explain OIDC.",
    "answer": "OpenID Connect (OIDC) federates authentication. Rather than storing AWS IAM keys or GCP JSON keys as static variables, the Runner retrieves a dynamic JWT token from GitLab and exchanges it with the Cloud Provider for short-lived IAM credentials.\n\n**Security Benefit**: Zero credentials stored in GitLab repository settings. Prevents credentials leakage.\n\n**Workload Identity Federation (GCP Example)**:\n```yaml\ndeploy-gcp:\n  id_tokens:\n    GCP_JWT_TOKEN:\n      aud: https://iam.googleapis.com/projects/123/locations/global/workloadIdentityPools/my-pool/providers/my-provider\n  image: google/cloud-sdk:latest\n  script:\n    - echo \"${GCP_JWT_TOKEN}\" > /tmp/jwt.txt\n    - gcloud iam workload-identity-pools create-cred-config ... --credential-source-file=/tmp/jwt.txt\n    - gcloud auth login --cred-file=/tmp/gcp-creds.json\n    - gsutil cp dist/* gs://my-prod-bucket/\n```",
    "tags": [
      "OIDC",
      "workload identity",
      "gcp",
      "security"
    ]
