    "id": "gitlab-46",
    "category": "GitLab",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "Write a job configuration that compiles a library (npm or PyPI) and publishes it to the project's GitLab Package Registry. Detail the auth tokens and endpoints used.",
    "answer": "This configuration uses NPM registry authentication with the built-in `$CI_JOB_TOKEN` to publish package dependencies to the GitLab project registry.\n\n**GitLab CI Job (`.gitlab-ci.yml`)**:\n```yaml\npublish-package:\n  stage: deploy\n  image: node:18-alpine\n  script:\n    # Set up registry configuration pointing to GitLab instance\n    - echo \"@my-scope:registry=${CI_API_V4_URL}/projects/${CI_PROJECT_ID}/packages/npm/\" > .npmrc\n    # Authenticate using the temporary runner job token\n    - echo \"${CI_API_V4_URL#https:}/projects/${CI_PROJECT_ID}/packages/npm/:_authToken=${CI_JOB_TOKEN}\" >> .npmrc\n    - npm install\n    - npm run build\n    # Publish the library package\n    - npm publish\n  rules:\n    - if: $CI_COMMIT_TAG # Publish only when tag is created\n```\nKey details: `${CI_API_V4_URL#https:}` extracts the host address, ensuring credentials align with registry endpoints.",
