    "id": "gitlab-47",
    "category": "GitLab",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "question": "Provide the detailed configuration to authenticate a GitLab Runner with HashiCorp Vault using JWT. Include the Vault auth role and the GitLab CI job configuration.",
    "answer": "This setup establishes secure trust between GitLab CI and HashiCorp Vault using OpenID Connect.\n\n**1. HashiCorp Vault Configuration Commands (CLI)**:\n```bash\n# Enable JWT Auth\nvault auth enable jwt\n\n# Configure connection to GitLab OIDC endpoint\nvault write auth/jwt/config \\\n    oidc_discovery_url=\"https://gitlab.com\" \\\n    bound_issuer=\"https://gitlab.com\"\n\n# Create a role linking GitLab project to a policy\nvault write auth/jwt/role/gitlab-prod-role \\\n    role_type=\"jwt\" \\\n    policies=\"prod-db-policy\" \\\n    token_ttl=\"1h\" \\\n    bound_claims=\"{\\\"project_id\\\": \\\"98765\\\", \\\"ref\\\": \\\"main\\\", \\\"ref_type\\\": \\\"branch\\\"}\" \\\n    user_claim=\"user_email\"\n```\n\n**2. GitLab Job Configuration (`.gitlab-ci.yml`)**:\n```yaml\nget-vault-secret:\n  stage: build\n  image: hashicorp/vault:latest\n  id_tokens:\n    VAULT_JWT_TOKEN:\n      aud: https://gitlab.com\n  script:\n    - export VAULT_TOKEN=$(vault write -field=token auth/jwt/login role=gitlab-prod-role jwt=$VAULT_JWT_TOKEN)\n    - DB_PASSWORD=$(vault kv get -field=password secret/data/prod/db)\n    - echo \"Fetched password successfully.\"\n```",
