    "question": "What is Continuous Machine Learning (CML) and how does it automate model validation reports in GitHub Actions/GitLab CI?",
    "answer": "Continuous Machine Learning (CML) is an open-source library that helps implement CI/CD for machine learning projects. It runs inside CI runners to generate visual model comparison reports (metrics, confusion matrices, loss curves) and post them directly as comments on Pull/Merge Requests.\n\nHow it Works in a CI Pipeline:\n1. **Trigger**: Developer creates a PR with model training code changes.\n2. **Run**: The CI runner executes the training script using DVC to pull the dataset, trains the model, and outputs a `metrics.txt` and `confusion_matrix.png`.\n3. **Report Generation**: The CI runner invokes CML CLI commands to format these files into a markdown report:\n   ```bash\n   cml readme-create --publish --markdown >> report.md\n   cml send-comment report.md\n   ```\n4. **Feedback**: CML uses git credentials to comment on the PR, allowing reviewers to verify performance changes before merging.",
