    "question": "Explain the role of ML Metadata (MLMD) in Kubeflow. Why is it important to track lineage of pipeline runs?",
    "answer": "ML Metadata (MLMD) is a library for tracking and retrieving metadata associated with ML developer workflows. It records details about pipelines, executions (runs), and artifacts (datasets, models, metrics).\n\nImportance of Lineage Tracking:\n- **Reproducibility**: If a model in production behaves anomalously, MLMD allows engineers to trace back and identify the exact dataset version, hyperparameters, and code commit used to generate it.\n- **Compliance & Auditing**: In regulated industries (e.g., finance, healthcare), companies must prove how a model was trained and validate that no restricted data was used.\n- **Debugging**: Easily locate which component in a complex pipeline failed or produced bad data by inspecting the intermediate artifact properties stored in the MLMD database.",
