    "question": "How do you partition a physical A100 GPU into multiple MIG instances and expose them to Kubernetes using the NVIDIA GPU Operator?",
    "answer": "To partition and allocate MIG instances:\n\n1. **Enable MIG on the Host GPU**:\n   `nvidia-smi -i 0 -mig 1` (Enables MIG on GPU 0).\n\n2. **Create MIG Profiles**:\n   List available profiles: `nvidia-smi mig -lgip`.\n   Create specific partitions (e.g., one 3g.40gb profile and two 1g.10gb profiles):\n   ```bash\n   nvidia-smi mig -cgi 9,19,19 -C\n   ```\n\n3. **Expose to Kubernetes using NVIDIA GPU Operator**:\n   Configure the GPU Operator's ClusterPolicy to enable MIG. The operator automatically labels nodes containing MIG instances.\n   Apply a MIG geometry configuration in the values file:\n   ```yaml\n   mig:\n     strategy: mixed\n   ```\n   The operator exposes the resources as K8s allocatable capacity (e.g., `nvidia.com/mig-1g.10gb: 2` and `nvidia.com/mig-3g.40gb: 1`).\n\n4. **Request in Pod Pod Spec**:\n   ```yaml\n   resources:\n     limits:\n       nvidia.com/mig-1g.10gb: \"1\"\n   ```",
