    "question": "Write a sample Feast 'feature_store.yaml' configuration that defines BigQuery as the offline store and Redis as the online store.",
    "answer": "Feast orchestrates the synchronization of features. The `feature_store.yaml` configures the backend engines.\n\nSample configuration:\n\n```yaml\nproject: ad_recommendation\nregistry: gs://my-feast-bucket/registry.db\nprovider: gcp\noffline_store:\n  type: bigquery\n  dataset: feast_features\n  project: my-gcp-project\nonline_store:\n  type: redis\n  connection_string: rediss://default:my_secure_password@my-redis-host:6379/0\n  ssl: true\n  key_ttl: 2592000 # 30 days\n```\n\nExplanation:\n- `registry`: Stores the schema/definitions of features in GCP Storage.\n- `offline_store`: BigQuery is queried when generating historical training data.\n- `online_store`: Redis is populated during feature ingestion (`feast materialize-incremental`) and queried for low-latency inference vectors.",
