    "question": "How do you automate model promotion from 'Staging' to 'Production' using MLflow Webhooks and a GitLab CI/CD pipeline?",
    "answer": "Automating promotion prevents manual errors and ensures validation tests run before a model goes live:\n\n1. **MLflow Webhook Configuration**: Register a webhook in MLflow that triggers whenever a new model version is transitioned to 'Staging' or a registration event occurs.\n   ```bash\n   curl -X POST -H \"Authorization: Bearer $MLFLOW_TRACKING_TOKEN\" \\\n     https://mlflow-server/api/2.0/mlflow/webhooks/create \\\n     -d '{\n       \"model_name\": \"fraud-detection-classifier\",\n       \"events\": [\"MODEL_VERSION_TRANSITIONED_TO_STAGING\"],\n       \"http_url_spec\": {\n         \"url\": \"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/12345/ref/main/trigger/pipeline\"\n       }\n     }'\n   ```\n2. **GitLab CI/CD Pipeline (Validation & Promotion)**:\n   The webhook triggers a pipeline. The job runs a python script that:\n   - Connects to MLflow and downloads the 'Staging' model.\n   - Evaluates the model against a gold-standard validation dataset.\n   - If the new model beats the current Production model (e.g., higher ROC-AUC and latency < 5ms):\n     - Calls MLflow API to promote the version to 'Production' and demotes the old version to 'Archived'.\n     - Triggers an ArgoCD webhook to sync the production manifest pointing to the new model URI.",
