    "question": "Write a snippet of a Ray Cluster configuration (`ray-cluster.yaml`) that configures autoscaling with mixed CPU and GPU spot instances.",
    "answer": "A Ray cluster uses a head node to manage scheduling and worker nodes that scale dynamically depending on resource demands.\n\nSample YAML configuration snippet:\n\n```yaml\ncluster_name: ray-gpu-cluster\nmax_workers: 10\nprovider:\n  type: aws\n  region: us-west-2\nhead_node:\n  InstanceType: m5.2xlarge\n  ImageId: ami-0c02fb55956c7d316\nworker_nodes:\n  gpu_workers:\n    min_workers: 0\n    max_workers: 5\n    InstanceType: g4dn.4xlarge # 1 NVIDIA T4 GPU\n    InstanceMarketOptions:\n      MarketType: spot\n    resources:\n      CPU: 16\n      GPU: 1\n  cpu_workers:\n    min_workers: 1\n    max_workers: 5\n    InstanceType: m5.2xlarge\n    InstanceMarketOptions:\n      MarketType: spot\n    resources:\n      CPU: 8\n```\n\nDesign Tip:\n- Ray's autoscaler automatically provisions `gpu_workers` when a job requested in code specifies `@ray.remote(num_gpus=1)`, and spins them down when idle, minimizing spot billing costs.",
