    "category": "MLOps",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "Write a Prometheus Alertmanager rule configuration that triggers a critical alert when model response latency (p99) exceeds 200ms.",
    "answer": "This Alertmanager rule monitors model endpoints by calculating P99 latency from a Prometheus histogram metric (`http_request_duration_seconds_bucket`).\n\nSample Prometheus Rules YAML:\n\n```yaml\ngroups:\n- name: model-latency-alerts\n  rules:\n  - alert: ModelP99LatencyTooHigh\n    expr: histogram_quantile(0.99, sum(rate(http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])) by (le, model_name)) > 0.2\n    for: 2m\n    labels:\n      severity: critical\n      tier: mlops\n    annotations:\n      summary: \"Model {{ $labels.model_name }} is experiencing high latency\"\n      description: \"The P99 latency for model {{ $labels.model_name }} is above 200ms (current value: {{ $value }}s) for the last 2 minutes.\"\n```\n\nExplanation:\n- `histogram_quantile(0.99, ...)`: Computes the 99th percentile of request latencies over a 5-minute rolling window.\n- `for: 2m`: Wait 2 minutes before firing to prevent alerts on temporary spikes.",
