    "id": "obs-6",
    "category": "Observability",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "What are Grafana template variables, and how do they improve dashboard usability and performance?",
    "answer": "Grafana template variables are placeholders dynamically populated by queries (e.g., fetching a list of Kubernetes namespaces or server hostnames) that appear as dropdown menus at the top of a dashboard.\n\nUsability Improvements:\n- Avoids hardcoding: Instead of creating 50 separate dashboards for 50 servers, one template dashboard is created, and users select the target server from a dropdown.\n- Multiselect and Ad-hoc filters: Users can select multiple hosts or dynamically add filter criteria without editing the dashboard layout.\n\nPerformance Improvements:\n- Variables can be used to scope queries down, ensuring Grafana only queries the TSDB for the selected target, rather than requesting global metrics which causes timeout and high CPU usage on the datasource.",
