    "id": "obs-14",
    "category": "Observability",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "What are the standard ports and protocols used by the OpenTelemetry Protocol (OTLP)?",
    "answer": "The OpenTelemetry Protocol (OTLP) natively supports both gRPC and HTTP/JSON transports. The standardized ports are:\n\n- OTLP/gRPC:\n  - Port: `4317`\n  - Protocol: HTTP/2 over TLS or plaintext.\n  - Purpose: High-performance, low-latency binary serialization (Protocol Buffers).\n\n- OTLP/HTTP:\n  - Port: `4318`\n  - Protocol: HTTP/1.1 or HTTP/2, sending payload formatted as JSON or Protobuf binary.\n  - Purpose: Compatibility with web browsers, proxies, and restricted network environments.\n\nOTel Collector and agents default to listening on these ports for incoming trace, metric, and log data.",
    "tags": [
      "OpenTelemetry",
      "OTLP",
      "Networking"
    ]
