    "question": "How do you configure trace-to-logs and logs-to-traces integration in Grafana? Detail the datasource adjustments required.",
    "answer": "To link Loki logs with Tempo traces, configure both datasources in Grafana's settings:\n\n1. Logs to Traces (Loki Configuration):\nUnder Loki datasource settings, add a 'Derived Fields' rule:\n- Name: `trace_id`\n- Regex: `(?:trace_id|traceId)=([a-f0-9]{32})`\n- Internal Link: Enable and select the 'Tempo' target datasource.\n- URL: Set to `${__value.raw}` to pass the extracted trace ID directly to Tempo.\nThis adds a clickable button next to any log line containing a trace ID, opening the trace in Tempo.\n\n2. Traces to Logs (Tempo Configuration):\nUnder Tempo datasource settings, configure the 'Trace to logs' section:\n- Data source: Select the 'Loki' datasource.\n- Tags: Add tags like `service.name` or `app` to map spans to log streams.\n- Filter by trace ID: Enable this. When you click 'Go to logs' in a Tempo span, Grafana generates a LogQL query like `{app=\"payment-service\"} |=\"<trace-id>\"` to pull matching logs.",
