    "id": "sec-21",
    "category": "Security",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "Write a Kubernetes NetworkPolicy that isolates a database pod labeled 'role: db' in namespace 'prod', allowing ingress traffic ONLY from a frontend pod labeled 'role: frontend' on TCP port 5432.",
    "answer": "Apply this NetworkPolicy in the 'prod' namespace to enforce traffic flow controls:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: db-ingress-restriction\n  namespace: prod\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      role: db\n  policyTypes:\n    - Ingress\n  ingress:\n    - from:\n        - podSelector:\n            matchLabels:\n              role: frontend\n      ports:\n        - protocol: TCP\n          port: 5432\n```\n\nHow it works:\n- `podSelector.matchLabels.role: db`: Selects the target database pod to secure.\n- `ingress.from.podSelector.matchLabels.role: frontend`: Explicitly whitelist only pods carrying the `role: frontend` label in the same namespace.\n- `ingress.ports`: Restricts the incoming traffic strictly to TCP port 5432 (default PostgreSQL port). All other ports and source traffic are blocked.",
    "tags": [
      "Kubernetes",
      "NetworkPolicy",
      "YAML",
      "Network-Security"
    ]
