    "id": "tb-8",
    "category": "Troubleshooting",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "A CI/CD pipeline job using Docker-in-Docker (DinD) fails with: 'Cannot connect to the Docker daemon at unix:///var/run/docker.sock. Is the docker daemon running?'. How do you resolve this?",
    "answer": "This error occurs because the runner container executing the pipeline job does not have access to a running Docker daemon socket or daemon service.\n\n### Resolutions:\n1. **Mount the Docker Socket**: If running a self-hosted runner, ensure the host's `/var/run/docker.sock` is mounted into the runner container:\n   `volumes = [\"/var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock\"]` in the runner config.\n2. **Enable Privileged Mode**: Docker-in-Docker requires privileged container access to start a nested daemon. Set `privileged = true` in the runner's configuration.\n3. **Use Docker-in-Docker Service**: In GitLab CI, configure the DinD service:\n   ```yaml\n   services:\n     - name: docker:dind\n   variables:\n     DOCKER_HOST: tcp://docker:2375\n     DOCKER_TLS_CERTDIR: \"\"\n   ```",
