    "id": "code-5",
    "category": "Scripting",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "question": "Write a Python script using `boto3` to list all objects in an AWS S3 bucket named `my-company-backups` that are larger than 10 Megabytes (MB). Output the key name and size in MB.",
    "answer": "You can interact with S3 objects using the boto3 client or resource APIs. Since buckets can contain thousands of keys, we should paginate or iterate cleanly.\n\n### Python Script:\n```python\nimport boto3\n\ns3 = boto3.client('s3')\nbucket_name = 'my-company-backups'\nlimit_bytes = 10 * 1024 * 1024  # 10 MB in bytes\n\ntry:\n    # Using list_objects_v2 paginator to handle buckets with >1000 keys\n    paginator = s3.get_paginator('list_objects_v2')\n    pages = paginator.paginate(Bucket=bucket_name)\n\n    for page in pages:\n        # Check if bucket is empty\n        if 'Contents' not in page:\n            print(\"Bucket is empty.\")\n            break\n\n        for obj in page['Contents']:\n            size_bytes = obj['Size']\n            if size_bytes > limit_bytes:\n                size_mb = size_bytes / (1024 * 1024)\n                print(f\"Key: {obj['Key']} | Size: {size_mb:.2f} MB\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error listing S3 objects: {e}\")\n```",
    "tags": [
      "python",
      "aws",
      "s3",
      "boto3"
    ]
