    "question": "Write a Python function using `boto3` to upload a large file (e.g., 5GB+) to an S3 bucket. The function must use S3 Multipart Upload via boto3's `TransferConfig` to optimize the upload speed by utilizing multiple concurrent threads and enabling automatic retries.",
    "answer": "Boto3 provides `boto3.s3.transfer.TransferConfig` to configure multi-threaded, multipart uploads automatically.\n\n### Python Code:\n```python\nimport os\nimport boto3\nfrom boto3.s3.transfer import TransferConfig\nfrom botocore.exceptions import ClientError\n\ndef upload_large_file(local_path, bucket, s3_key):\n    # Threshold: 100MB. Files larger than this will use multipart upload.\n    # Max concurrency: 10 threads.\n    config = TransferConfig(\n        multipart_threshold=100 * 1024 * 1024,\n        max_concurrency=10,\n        multipart_chunksize=50 * 1024 * 1024,\n        use_threads=True\n    )\n    \n    s3_client = boto3.client('s3')\n    \n    try:\n        print(f\"Starting upload of {local_path} to s3://{bucket}/{s3_key}\")\n        s3_client.upload_file(\n            Filename=local_path,\n            Bucket=bucket,\n            Key=s3_key,\n            Config=config\n        )\n        print(\"Upload completed successfully!\")\n        return True\n    except ClientError as e:\n        print(f\"Upload failed: {e}\")\n        return False\n```",
