    "question": "Write a Python script using the `google-cloud-storage` library to upload all files matching the pattern `*.tar.gz` from a local directory `/var/backups/` to a Google Cloud Storage bucket named `production-backups-gcs`.",
    "answer": "You can upload files to GCP Storage using the official `google-cloud-storage` package.\n\n### Python Script:\n```python\nimport glob\nimport os\nfrom google.cloud import storage\nfrom google.api_core.exceptions import GoogleAPIError\n\ndef upload_backups(local_dir, bucket_name):\n    try:\n        # Initializes client using credentials from GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS env var\n        client = storage.Client()\n        bucket = client.bucket(bucket_name)\n        \n        search_pattern = os.path.join(local_dir, '*.tar.gz')\n        files_to_upload = glob.glob(search_pattern)\n        \n        if not files_to_upload:\n            print(f\"No backups found in {local_dir}\")\n            return\n            \n        for file_path in files_to_upload:\n            blob_name = os.path.basename(file_path)\n            blob = bucket.blob(blob_name)\n            \n            print(f\"Uploading {file_path} to gs://{bucket_name}/{blob_name}...\")\n            blob.upload_from_filename(file_path)\n            print(f\"Success: {blob_name} uploaded.\")\n            \n    except GoogleAPIError as e:\n        print(f\"GCP storage API error occurred: {e}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"An error occurred: {e}\")\n\nupload_backups('/var/backups/', 'production-backups-gcs')\n```",
