    "question": "Write a Python script using `boto3` to generate a secure S3 Presigned URL for an object `reports/Q2.pdf` inside bucket `company-financials`. The URL must expire in exactly 15 minutes, allowing a client to download the file directly via HTTPS without possessing AWS credentials.",
    "answer": "Presigned URLs grant temporary access to objects using the permissions of the IAM identity generating the URL.\n\n### Python Script:\n```python\nimport boto3\nfrom botocore.exceptions import ClientError\n\ndef generate_download_url(bucket_name, object_name, expiration_seconds=900):\n    s3_client = boto3.client('s3')\n    try:\n        # Generate presigned URL for GET request\n        url = s3_client.generate_presigned_url(\n            'get_object',\n            Params={\n                'Bucket': bucket_name,\n                'Key': object_name\n            },\n            ExpiresIn=expiration_seconds\n        )\n        return url\n    except ClientError as e:\n        print(f\"Error generating URL: {e}\")\n        return None\n\n# Expiration: 15 minutes = 900 seconds\npresigned_url = generate_download_url('company-financials', 'reports/Q2.pdf', 900)\nif presigned_url:\n    print(f\"Presigned URL (valid for 15 mins):\\n{presigned_url}\")\n```",
