    "answer": "The `kubernetes` SDK client interacts directly with the Kube-API server, authenticating either in-cluster or via kubeconfig.\n\n### Python Script:\n```python\nfrom kubernetes import client, config\nfrom kubernetes.client.rest import ApiException\n\ndef list_billing_pods():\n    try:\n        # Load local kubeconfig. Use load_incluster_config() if running inside a pod.\n        config.load_kube_config()\n        \n        v1 = client.CoreV1Api()\n        namespace = 'billing'\n        \n        print(f\"Fetching pods in namespace: {namespace}\")\n        pods = v1.list_namespaced_pod(namespace)\n        \n        for pod in pods.items:\n            pod_name = pod.metadata.name\n            pod_ip = pod.status.pod_ip or 'No-IP'\n            phase = pod.status.phase\n            \n            print(f\"Pod: {pod_name} | IP: {pod_ip} | Phase: {phase}\")\n            \n    except ApiException as e:\n        print(f\"Kubernetes API exception: {e}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"An error occurred: {e}\")\n\nlist_billing_pods()\n```",
