    "id": "code-32",
    "category": "Scripting",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "Write a Python CLI tool using `argparse` that takes a mandatory string argument `-e` (environment: staging/production), an optional boolean flag `--dry-run`, and an optional integer `-t` (timeout, defaults to 30). Add validation to reject any environment string other than staging/production.",
    "answer": "The `argparse` library manages CLI argument input types and auto-generates help documents.\n\n### Python Script:\n```python\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Production deployment CLI tool.\")\n    \n    # Mandatory environment with choices validation\n    parser.add_argument(\n        '-e', '--environment',\n        required=True,\n        choices=['staging', 'production'],\n        help=\"Target deployment environment (staging/production)\"\n    )\n    \n    # Optional flag (action='store_true' sets it to True if present)\n    parser.add_argument(\n        '--dry-run',\n        action='store_true',\n        help=\"Perform a simulation run without modifications\"\n    )\n    \n    # Optional integer argument with default\n    parser.add_argument(\n        '-t', '--timeout',\n        type=int,\n        default=30,\n        help=\"Operation timeout in seconds (default: 30)\"\n    )\n    \n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    \n    print(f\"Executing script on: {args.environment}\")\n    print(f\"Dry Run active: {args.dry_run}\")\n    print(f\"Timeout limit: {args.timeout}s\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n```",
