    "id": "code-33",
    "category": "Scripting",
    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "question": "Write a Bash script that declares an array of 5 server IP addresses. It should loop through them, run a `nc` ping command to check if port 22 (SSH) is reachable with a 2-second timeout, and collect any failing server IPs into a secondary array. Finally, output the count and list of failed servers.",
    "answer": "Bash supports indexed arrays which can be instantiated and appended to using the `+=` operator.\n\n### Bash Script:\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n\nservers=(\"10.0.1.5\" \"10.0.1.6\" \"10.0.1.7\" \"10.0.1.8\" \"10.0.1.9\")\ndeclare -a failed_servers=()\n\nfor ip in \"${servers[@]}\"; do\n    echo \"Checking ${ip}...\"\n    # nc -z -w2 checks port availability with a 2-second timeout\n    if ! nc -z -w2 \"${ip}\" 22 >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n        echo \"[FAIL] Server ${ip} is unreachable on port 22.\"\n        failed_servers+=(\"${ip}\")\n    else\n        echo \"[OK] Server ${ip} is reachable.\"\n    fi\ndone\n\nif [[ \"${#failed_servers[@]}\" -gt 0 ]]; then\n    echo \"[ALERT] ${#failed_servers[@]} servers failed health check:\"\n    for ip in \"${failed_servers[@]}\"; do\n        echo \"  - ${ip}\"\n    done\nelse\n    echo \"All servers passed health checks.\"\nfi\n```",
